FBIS4-33105 "drlat106_k_94001" FBIS-LAT-94-106 Daily Report 2 Jun 1994 SOUTH AMERICA Argentina Israel's Peres Visits, Meets With Menem Israel's Peres Visits, Meets With Menem TA0206062294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0600 GMT 2 Jun 94 TA0206062294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Hebrew BFN [Text] Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres spent a lightning, four-hour visit in Buenos Aires last night. The foreign minister conferred with Argentine President Carlos Menem and briefed him about the autonomy agreement with the Palestinians. After the meeting, Minister Peres told reporters that Israel has evidence that a foreign country was involved in the explosion at the Israeli Embassy in Buenos Aires two years ago. He added that Israel will publicize the details after it completes its investigation into the incident. Twenty-two people were killed and many wounded in the explosion. Minister Peres also denounced the continued presence of Nazi criminals in Argentina.
